<hr>
<strong>WORKS CITED</strong>
<br><br>
Add a &#8216;Works Cited&#8217; entry at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br><br>
A description of the source can be added, if it is needed for clarity, at the end of the Works Cited entry. 
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Creator or owner of image. &#34;Title of image.&#34; <em>Title of book</em>, Publisher, year of publication, page number. Description. 
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Creator or owner of image">Tschichold, Jan</span>.
	<span class="hover" title="Title of image">"Die Frau Ohne Namen." (The Woman without a Name).</span>
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of book">Clean New World: Culture, Politics, and Graphic Design</span></em>,
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">MIT P</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2001</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Page number">p. 32</span>.
	<span class="hover" title="Description">Offset lithograph poster</span>.
</blockquote>
